# JA4proxy-testing — 18-B / 18-B-2 CVE allowlist
#
# Every non-comment line is a CVE accepted for a bounded window. Each
# CVE MUST be preceded by an `# expires: YYYY-MM-DD` comment (blank
# lines reset the block). scripts/ci/check_image_scan.py fails if any
# entry is expired — forcing a decision to fix, re-justify with a new
# expiry, or remove.
#
# Severity response times (PHASE_18 acceptance matrix):
#   CRITICAL → decision within 7 days,  fix within 30
#   HIGH     → decision within 30 days, fix within 90
#
# Since 18-B-2, `scripts/ci/scan_images.sh` runs a single
# `--severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1` pass, so a new HIGH reddens
# the `image-scan` job the same way a CRITICAL does. The job is
# advisory on `main` (not a required status check — see the comment
# at `.github/workflows/ci.yml:43-47`); a red run is a merge-blocker
# signal in PR review, not a mechanical gate. Anything here is
# opted-in *explicitly* with a bounded expiry.

# Phase 20 P2-11: expiries staggered across 2026-05-05 → 2026-05-19 by
# upstream image so that one big-bang red day becomes five spaced
# decisions. All justifications are unchanged; only the dates moved.

# === CRITICALs ========================================================
# caddy:2-alpine — smallstep/certificates + grpc-go. Caddy's cert
# handling and gRPC surface are not on our public path (HAProxy
# terminates TLS as passthrough; Caddy only serves the static honeypot
# after JA4proxy). Fixes require upstream caddy image refresh.
# expires: 2026-05-05
CVE-2026-30836
# expires: 2026-05-05
CVE-2026-33186

# grafana/grafana:latest — jackc/pgx/v5 Postgres-driver memory-safety
# flaw (fixed in v5.9.0). Exploit requires Grafana to connect to an
# attacker-controlled Postgres server; this deployment only configures
# Prometheus + Loki data sources (see deploy/roles/06-monitoring/),
# not Postgres. Awaiting upstream grafana image refresh.
# expires: 2026-05-12
CVE-2026-33816

# prom/blackbox-exporter:latest — Go 1.25.5 crypto/tls cert-validation
# flaw (fixed in 1.24.13 / 1.25.7). Blackbox probes known targets over
# HTTPS from the monitoring network; exploit requires MITM position on
# the probe path. Awaiting upstream image refresh.
# expires: 2026-05-19
CVE-2025-68121

# === HIGHs: Go stdlib 2026 series =====================================
# Span caddy, grafana, loki, promtail, blackbox. Fixes land only when
# each upstream rebases its image onto Go 1.25.9 / 1.26.2. Five stdlib
# CVEs, mostly DoS / edge-case validation — none reachable from our
# honeypot path as configured. (Fate-shared: all five clear together
# when the toolchain bump lands.)
# expires: 2026-05-07
CVE-2026-25679
# expires: 2026-05-07
CVE-2026-27137
# expires: 2026-05-07
CVE-2026-32280
# expires: 2026-05-07
CVE-2026-32282
# expires: 2026-05-07
CVE-2026-33810

# === HIGHs: Go stdlib 2025 series (blackbox on 1.25.5) ===============
# Same exposure argument as CVE-2025-68121 above.
# expires: 2026-05-19
CVE-2025-61726
# expires: 2026-05-19
CVE-2025-61728

# === HIGHs: Go stdlib 2026 series on blackbox (1.25.5) ===============
# crypto/x509 cert-chain DoS and TLS key-update handling, fixed in
# 1.25.9 / 1.26.2. Same probes-only exposure argument as above.
# expires: 2026-05-19
CVE-2026-32281
# expires: 2026-05-19
CVE-2026-32283

# === HIGHs: embedded Go deps ==========================================
# go-jose (caddy, loki): JWE/JWT parsing flaw. Not on our public path.
# expires: 2026-05-14
CVE-2026-34986
# opentelemetry-go otel/sdk: BSD-only kenv absolute-path issue. Not BSD.
# expires: 2026-05-14
CVE-2026-39883
# buger/jsonparser (prometheus): stack overflow on crafted JSON from
# scrape targets. Our scrape targets are internal + pinned.
# expires: 2026-05-14
CVE-2026-32285
# docker/moby authz bypass (prometheus, grafana, promtail service
# discovery): requires docker socket access, which these containers do
# not have (we do not mount /var/run/docker.sock into any of them).
# expires: 2026-05-14
CVE-2026-34040

# === HIGHs: Alpine base packages in grafana/grafana ===================
# Fixed upstream in Alpine; grafana:latest needs a rebuild cycle.
# expires: 2026-05-12
CVE-2026-28390
# expires: 2026-05-12
CVE-2026-40200
